properties.TTIPNOTES: This District is considered under Open Space Development: A residential (or non- residential) subdivision in which a specified area of open space is protected as a condition of approval. The concept of OSD is that a parcel shall be recognized for the value of its open space – be that for agricultural, wildlife habitat, recreational, scenic or another value; and that open space be intentionally reserved free from development.
